SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1134
By Briggs
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Sophia Chen, 2026
Valedictorian of Farragut High School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to pay
tribute to those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to
academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Sophia Chen is one such exceptional student, who was recently named the
Valedictorian of the 2026 graduating class at Farragut High School; and
WHEREAS, through diligent study, steady composure during examinations, and
steadfast commitment of time and talent, Ms. Chen has achieved outstanding academic
success and joined the ranks of the best and brightest students in Tennessee and our country;
and
WHEREAS, in her remarkable high school career, Sophia Chen has earned an
exemplary grade point average of 4.785 while participating in numerous extracurricular
activities, including HOSA, Mu Alpha Theta, tennis, and Youth in Government; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Chen is the president of the Science Club, the vice president of Youth
in Government, and a violinist in the Knoxville Symphony Youth Orchestra; and
WHEREAS, she has earned numerous accolades, including placing as a semifinalist
twice in the USA Biology Olympiad, being on the Tennessee Science Bowl champion team
twice, receiving Youth in Government Best Speaker awards, and being selected as a National
Merit Finalist and a Regeneron Science Talent Search Scholar; and
WHEREAS, Sophia Chen also performed research at the Cold Spring Harbor Laboratory
for two years; and
SJR1134
017398
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Ms. Chen's favorite pastimes are baking, playing and writing crossword
puzzles, and working on political campaigns; and
WHEREAS, her display of intellectual aptitude and ambition surely bodes well for her
future success; and
WHEREAS, Sophia Chen's noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of pride for
her parents, Feng Chen and Ju Guan, her school, and her community; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Chen's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the respect,
admiration, and commendation of this General Assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby commend and honor Sophia Chen of
Farragut High School on being named the 2026 Valedictorian, salute her impressive academic
achievement, and extend to her our best wishes for a happy, successful future.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
